divs: Sighting DetailsI was walking my dog one night late in the evening. I looked up in the sky to see a satellite inching along in the sky among the trees. As soon as I identified the satellite I saw an orange ball high in the sky among the stars make a 360 degree circle within two seconds it was gone. It was a little hard to see afterward as if I was seeing the stars right in front of me. My vision was kind of hazy.
Summary: Orange ball in the sky, high in the stars.
